1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.899
{"en":"--- lesson 25  The Cutty Sark “","ch":"卡蒂萨克”号帆船 "}

2
00:00:04.049 --> 00:00:12.180
{"en":"One of the most famous sailing ships of the nineteenth century,  the Cutty Sark,  can still be seen at Greenwich. ^ ","ch":"人们在格林威治仍可看到19世纪最有名的帆船之一“卡蒂萨克”号。  "}

3
00:00:12.330 --> 00:00:17.979
{"en":"She stands on dry land and is visited by thousands of people each year. ^ ","ch":"它停在陆地上， 每年接待成千上万的参观者。  "}

4
00:00:18.129 --> 00:00:23.909
{"en":"She serves as an impressive reminder of the great ships of the past. ^ ","ch":"它给人们留下深刻的印象， 使人们回忆起历史上的巨型帆船，  "}

5
00:00:24.059 --> 00:00:34.985
{"en":"Before they were replaced by steamships,  sailing vessels like the Cutty Sark were used to carry tea from China and wool from Australia. ^ ","ch":"在蒸汽船取代帆船之前。 “卡蒂萨克”号之类的帆船被用来从中国运回茶叶， 从澳大利亚运回羊毛。  "}

6
00:00:35.135 --> 00:00:40.993
{"en":"The Cutty Sark was one of the fastest sailing ships that has ever been built. ^ “","ch":"卡蒂萨克”号是帆船制造史上建造的最快的一艘帆船。  "}

7
00:00:41.143 --> 00:00:45.826
{"en":"The only other ship to match her was the Thermopylae. ^ ","ch":"唯一可以与之一比高低的是“塞姆皮雷”号帆船。  "}

8
00:00:45.976 --> 00:00:55.386
{"en":"Both these ships set out from Shanghai on June 18th,  1872 on an exciting race to England. ^ ","ch":"两船于1872年6月18日同时从上海启航驶往英国， 途中展开了一场激烈的比赛。  "}

9
00:00:55.536 --> 00:01:02.309
{"en":"This race,  which went on for exactly four months,  was the last of its kind. ^ ","ch":"这场比赛持续了整整4个月， 是这类比赛中的最后一次，  "}

10
00:01:02.459 --> 00:01:09.989
{"en":"It marked the end of the great tradition of ships with sails and the beginning of a new era. ^ ","ch":"它标志着帆船伟大传统的结束与一个新纪元的开始。  "}

11
00:01:10.139 --> 00:01:21.483
{"en":"The first of the two ships to reach Java after the race had begun was the Thermopylae,  but on the Indian Ocean,  the Cutty Sark took the lead. ^ ","ch":"比赛开始后， “赛姆皮雷”号率先抵达爪哇岛。 但在印度洋上， “卡萨萨克”号驶到了前面。  "}

12
00:01:21.633 --> 00:01:29.267
{"en":"It seemed certain that she would be the first ship home,  but during the race she had a lot of bad luck. ^ ","ch":"看来， 它首先返抵英国是确信无疑的了， 但它却在比赛中连遭厄运。  "}

13
00:01:29.417 --> 00:01:36.869
{"en":"In August,  she was struck by a very heavy storm during which her rudder was torn away. ^ 8","ch":"月份“卡蒂萨克”号遭到一场特大风暴的袭击， 失去了一只舵。  "}

14
00:01:37.019 --> 00:01:43.164
{"en":"The Cutty Sark rolled from side to side and it became impossible to steer her. ^ ","ch":"船身左右摇晃， 无法操纵。  "}

15
00:01:43.314 --> 00:01:51.001
{"en":"A temporary rudder was made on board from spare planks and it was fitted with great difficulty. ^ ","ch":"船员用备用的木板在船上赶制了一只应急用的舵， 并克服重重困难将舵安装就位，  "}

16
00:01:51.151 --> 00:01:54.240
{"en":"This greatly reduced the speed of the ship, ^ ","ch":"这样一来， 大大降低了船的航速。  "}

17
00:01:54.390 --> 00:02:01.554
{"en":"for there was a danger that if she travelled too quickly,  this rudder would be torn away as well. ^ ","ch":"因为船不能开得太快， 否则就有危险， 应急舵也会被刮走。  "}

18
00:02:01.704 --> 00:02:05.865
{"en":"Because of this,  the Cutty Sark lost her lead. ^ ","ch":"因为这个缘故， “卡蒂萨克”号落到了后面。  "}

19
00:02:06.015 --> 00:02:12.761
{"en":"After crossing the Equator,  the captain called in at a port to have a new rudder fitted, ^ ","ch":"跨越赤道后， 船长将船停靠在一个港口， 在那儿换了一只舵。  "}

20
00:02:12.911 --> 00:02:18.299
{"en":"but by now the Thermopylae was over five hundred miles ahead. ^ ","ch":"但此时， “赛姆皮雷”号早已在500多英里之遥了。  "}

21
00:02:18.449 --> 00:02:26.110
{"en":"Though the new rudder was fitted at tremendous speed,  it was impossible for the Cutty Sark to win. ^ ","ch":"尽管换装新舵时分秒必争， 但“卡蒂萨克”号已经不可能取胜了，  "}

22
00:02:26.260 --> 00:02:30.394
{"en":"She arrived in England a week after the Thermopylae. ^ ","ch":"它抵达英国时比“塞姆皮雷”号晚了1个星期。  "}

23
00:02:30.544 --> 00:02:36.350
{"en":"Even this was remarkable,  considering that she had had so many delays. ^ ","ch":"但考虑到路上的多次耽搁，  "}

24
00:02:36.500 --> 00:02:43.429
{"en":"There is no doubt that if she had not lost her rudder she would have won the race easily. ^ ","ch":"这个成绩也已很不容易了。 毫无疑问， 如果中途没有失去舵，  “卡帝萨克”号肯定能在比赛中轻易夺冠。  "}

